ish to see companies held accountable for every social and environmental ill, whether of their making or not. But reasonable observers will see it as a creditable attempt to provide shareholders with more of the corporate information they need.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  is often regarded as a branch of public relations, a fashionable trend that has little to do with the creation of profit and shareholder value. In the hands of some of its exponents, it is.\par \par \uc2 But the thinking behind the OFR, which must accompany the annual report and accounts, is harder-headed. It is an attempt to get company managements to consider, and explain to shareholders, the possible risks to the business.\par \par \uc2 As the consultation document explains, a company that ignores possible damage to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  does more than irritate the green lobby; it puts the company's licence to operate at risk. The same goes for any other damage to its reputation, through unethical behaviour or practices that attract the opprobrium of customers or the wider community.\par \par \uc2 The strength of the consultation document is that it leaves the directors of the company to decide what risks are germane to its activities and need to be spelt out in detail. This means a company can say a particular risk is not relevant to its business, eliminating the need for virtuous and vacuous phrases on the subject.\par \par \uc2 This does not mean the consultation document is without its dangers. Knowingly or recklessly approving an OFR that does not comply with the law will be a criminal offence. The company's auditors will have to affirm that the directors prepared the OFR after "due and careful inquiry".\par \par \uc2 The Confederation of British Industry says this is too high a legal standard, equivalent to that required for financial information in a company prospectus. They would prefer the "true and fair view" standard of statutory accounts.\par \par \uc2 The government should give the CBI a sympathetic hearing. The aim is to ensure that directors set up a decent risk assessment process. They should not be turned into criminals if, after making every reasonable effort, the company suffers a serious environmental or reputational reverse they failed to predict. The exercise will have failed if companies conclude the OFR is best written by the lawyers rather than their managers. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | c13 : \uc2 Regulation/Government Policy\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard