justright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The "greening" of the financial sector has been gathering speed since the World Bank's "equator principles" were launched.\par \par \uc2 Successive banks have declared support for stringent commitments to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . But environmental activists are stepping up campaigns accusing banks of failing to implement their promises.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Citigroup and 25 other big financial institutions have signed the equator principles - an agreement to adhere to the International Finance Corporation's social and environmental safeguards.\par \par \uc2 The financial institutions celebrate the first anniversary of the principles today. "It is one of the most important things that the banking industry has done in the past couple of years," Chuck Prince, chief executive of Citigroup, told the Financial Times yesterday.\par \par \uc2 BankTrack, an international network of non-governmental organisations, has launched an attack on banks saying they have violated the agreement. The group said controversial projects had gone ahead unaltered in spite of the banks' support for safeguards.\par \par \uc2 "NGOs still have some hope for the principles," said Michelle Chan-Fishel of Friends of the Earth, a member of BankTrack. "But if the equator banks continue to finance controversial deals, pursue an anti- environmental lobbying agenda and cloak themselves in secrecy and unaccountability, public confidence will be irretrievably lost."\par \par \uc2 Mr Prince argued that Citigroup, a leader of the initiative, had been transparent and expected other banks to follow suit.\par \par \uc2 "We are disclosing our progress on equator principles and I believe that eventually more and more institutions will do that, so that the issue of transparency will become more and more resolved," he said.\par \par \uc2 "It's a constant dialogue (with environmental groups) over where the goalposts are. In some ways it's a little frustrating but in most ways it's a positive."\par \par \uc2 The BankTrack report cited the Baku-Tbilisi-Ceyhan (BTC) oil pipeline as an example of a transaction financed by equator banks in spite of accusations by NGOs that it violated ethical, legal and human rights standards.\par \par \uc2 The NGOs also criticised 11 equator banks for warning the World Bank not to accept a recommendation by the Extractive Industries\par \par \uc2 Review to phase out lending to coal and oil projects.\par \par \uc2 In spite of the activists' aggressive stance their campaigns have succeeded. Environmental groups and socially responsible investment funds turned their attention to the commercial banks about five years ago on the grounds that they were increasingly funding controversial projects avoided by public institutions such as the World Bank. Many of the biggest banks have yielded to pressure, keen to protect their reputations after recent financial scandals.\par \par \uc2 Peter Woicke, head of the IFC, yesterday accused some NGOs of being irresponsible and not having accountability themselves. He said the IFC had done more consultations on the BTC pipeline than any other project.\par \par \uc2 "We are not going to stop projectsjust because Friends of the Earth are against them while the vast majority of local NGOs are in favour," said Mr Woicke.\par \par \uc2 He said he hoped pension funds would now take a more agressive attitude on \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "If pension funds would focus a little more on sustainability that would force equity analysts to look at projects in a slightly different way."\par \par \uc2 Critics of the equator principles say controversial projects will still be able to get funding unless there is a critical mass of banks adopting the principles.\par \par \uc2 "I am a little disappointed that we have only had one other US bank join," said Mr Prince, who considers it important that investment banks join the project as well as finance banks. "I would strongly encourage other financial institutions in the US to join the equator principles."\par \par \uc2 Environmental groups have lobbied the US Securities and Exchange Commission to force companies to increase disclosure of environmental risk.\par \par \uc2 Mr Prince said Citigroup would welcome dialogue with regulators about increasing environmental rules but did not expect any changes over the next couple of years. Citigroup committed itself in January to initiatives with the Rainforest Action Network, an NGO, including special measures to protect ecologically or socially fragile areas. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i814 : \uc2 Banking | ibnk : \uc2 Banking/Credit\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widc