\trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2004 Dow Jones & Company, Inc. To see the edition in which this article appeared, click here  \uc2 http://awsj.com.hk/factiva-ns\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Tokyo -- INVESTING IN companies that incorporate responsible social and environmental policies is a hot concept in the U.S. and Europe. In fact, an entire sector of the global fund-management industry has developed around the idea that good corporate citizenship is good business, and rewarding for investors.  \par \par \uc2 Now, that trend is starting to gain traction in Japan as a series of corporate scandals spurs some investors to seek out socially responsible companies. Two stocks, Canon and Sompo Japan Insurance, look especially well positioned to benefit as a result.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Fund-management firms clearly see a future in the socially responsible investing movement. Japan's STB Asset Management set up its Japanese-equity Good Company investment trust in December. Last month, Nomura Asset Management established the Nomura Global SRI 100, which invests in companies from around the world that are included in the FTSE4Good Global 100 Index. Also last month, Daiwa Asset Management set up the Japanese-equity Daiwa SRI Fund.  \par \par \uc2 The new Morningstar Socially Responsible Investment Index, meanwhile, tracks the share performance of select Japanese companies based on their commitment to society, such as environmental care. In addition, four major global stock indexes that track socially responsible companies include Japanese stocks: the FTSE4Good Global Index, the FTSE4Good Global 100 Index, the Dow Jones Sustainability World Index and the Ethibel Sustainability Index Global.  \par \par \uc2 Canon is the only Japanese firm selected by all of the five indexes that track the sector. The maker of printers and cameras is known for promoting product recycling and using environmentally friendly substances in its products. Between June 2001 and May 2004, Canon's share rose 16%, outperforming the Topix index of all the Tokyo Stock Exchange's first section shares, which fell 13% during the three-year period.  \par \par \uc2 Sompo Japan, an insurance company created in July 2002 by the merger of Yasuda Fire & Marine Insurance and Nissan Fire & Marine Insurance, was chosen by four of the five indexes. The company offers \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 -related insurance products, such as car-insurance plans that offer a discount to drivers of "green" cars, and an "eco fund" -- an investment trust that tracks environmentally friendly companies. Its shares have gained 31% from July 2002 to May 2004. That beat the Topix's 11% rise over the same period. Tokyo research firm IntegreX, which rates companies on how socially responsible they are, also ranks Sompo Japan top among listed Japanese firms.  \par \par \uc2 Corporate responsibility isn't the only reason that shares of Canon and Sompo Japan are rising. Canon's net profit has more than doubled over the past three years, while Sompo Japan posted net profit of 55.09 billion yen ($503.9 million) for the year ended March 31, reversing a year-earlier net loss of 40.99 billion yen.  \par \par \uc2 Still, the stamp of approval from socially responsible investing indexes and research firms is appealing to a growing number of investment trusts and corporate pension funds these days. One possible reason: the rising number of corporate scandals that are rocking big Japanese companies long thought to be respectable.  \par \par \uc2 A decades-long coverup of defective parts by Mitsubishi Motors continues to catch headlines as more details of the scandal emerge. Doctored nuclear-reactor safety records at Tokyo Electric Power, as well a corporate-racketeering scandal at Seibu Railway, also have raised doubts about corporate Japan's ethics.  \par \par \uc2 To be sure, Japan's individual investors haven't yet caught the social responsibility bug. "In Japan, [individual investors'] mind-set is focused more on making money," said Norihiro Fujito, equity strategist at Mitsubishi Securities.  \par \par \uc2 And socially responsible investment funds in Japan have a long way to go to catch up with the U.S. and European markets. In the U.S. last year, these funds totaled an estimated $2.2 trillion, and added up to about 350 billion euros, or about $425 billion, in Europe. In contrast, socially responsible investment funds in Japan were worth about 103 billion yen at the end of March, according to Daiwa Investor Relations.  \par \par \uc2 Still, in a domestic survey conducted in March and April by Daiwa Investor Relations, 61% of the 81 fund managers and analysts polled said they expected socially responsible investing to grow in Japan.  \par \par \uc2 More companies in Japan are starting to cater to socially responsible investment funds. In a bid to improve their corporate-brand image, Sony, Ricoh and Matsushita Electric Industrial, among others, last year set up \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  divisions to promote awareness among investors and consumers about their contributions to society and to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 A Sony spokeswoman said the company's new division also keeps a tab on chemical substances used in each product it makes.  \par \par \uc2 -- From Dow Jones Newswires  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 cnon : \uc2 Canon Inc.\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd