bl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PG\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 Page 6\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2004 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Sustainability is all the rage in business schools across Europe and the US, with institutions incorporating \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  issues into the MBA curriculum.\par \par \uc2 However, the subject remains largely in the hands of management professors who are teaching the subject as part of more general corporate citizenship or social enterprise course material.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 One exception is a course in finance and sustainability to be launched this autumn at New York's Columbia Business School.\par \par \uc2 "It's a finance course, rather than a social enterprise course," explains its creator, Bruce Usher, adjunct professor of finance at Columbia and chief executive officer of EcoSecurities Group, a greenhouse gas advisory company.\par \par \uc2 "The concept is to teach students that the same mainstream financial tools that are used in other ways can be equally applied in dealing with sustainability issues."\par \par \uc2 The programme will cover four main areas:*Capital markets: how the principles and mechanisms of capital markets are being applied to environmental issues, such as climate change, via regimes such as the European Union Emissions Trading Scheme.*Commercial banking: applying the tools of retail banking to issues such as poverty, through micro-finance - in both the US and in developing countries and project finance in developing countries - and the community credits issued through programmes such as the US's Community Reinvestment Act, which requires banks and other lenders to give a certain percentage of their loans each year to businesses in economically deprived areas.*Investment management: looking at socially responsible investment in three areas - first, in public equity markets; second, through private equity, where investment organisations look to invest in enterprises that have sustainability objectives, such as renewable energy; and, finally, through venture capital, looking at funds that invest in start-ups with sustainability objectives.*Commercial investment banking: including the work of development banks such as the International Finance Corporation and the World Bank, as well as examples of project finance, such as the Equator Principles, an initiative providing a framework for banks to manage environmental and social issues in project financing.\par \par \uc2 The course, which will be offered as an elective to Columbia's full-time MBA students, will be case-based, says Prof Usher, and will include examples of both successes and failures. Cases will include successes such as the acid rain trading programme operated by Southern Company, a US utility, and Conservation International and its use of financial tools, such as debt-for-nature swaps.\par \par \uc2 There will also be case studies from the World Bank and the International Finance Corporation.\par \par \uc2 "I am a big believer that the case methodology is very effective at business school," says Prof Usher. "Cases demonstrate the real life application of these financial tools. It is one thing to say, theoretically, that this is how we are going to solve environmental problems, but it is quite another to manage the problem of acid rain more efficiently through the use of these tools."\par \par \uc2 The course is aimed at two groups of students. A number of participants will be mainstream finance students. "There are a lot of people in the finance community who are very interested in understanding how their work has an impact beyond the bottom line," says Prof Usher.\par \par \uc2 "Because finance can be a very powerful tool - a lot of activities do not happen without finance."\par \par \uc2 Also likely to take the programme are students interested in working in social enterprise, sustainability oriented organisations or the non-profit sector - and those who recognise that financial tools will help them in their career.\par \par \uc2 But while, for now, Columbia's finance and sustainability course remains among the few of its kind, Prof Usher believes greater attention is now being given to the subject.\par \par \uc2 He has partly seen this in student activity, not only with students demonstrating considerable interest in the course, but also in the growth of business schools' social enterprise clubs, which are attracting increasingly large numbers of members.\par \par \uc2 "What that says is that there is a change in the business \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and some of that change is coming from the top - from the leaders of large institutions," he says.\par \par \uc2 "But you are seeing a lot of change coming from the bottom, from students. And as these students enter the workforce, they will bring that learning and interest with them." \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i9831 : \uc2 Business Schools | i983 : \uc2 Educational Services | ibcs : \uc2 Business/Consumer Services\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \cl