par\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A successful bid for Marks and Spencer by Philip Green would threaten its reputation as a responsible retailer, Business in the Community, the business-led campaign for corporate responsibility, has claimed.\par \par \uc2 Stuart Rose, the new chief executive who is defending M&S against Mr Green, collected the company of the year award for M&S at the BITC's annual Awards for Excellence on Tuesday night.The retailer was praised for its "outstanding" impact on society in areas such as sustainable food production and labour standards among suppliers.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 "These aren't values by which Philip Green runs the business," said Julia Cleverdon, BITC chief executive, before the ceremony. "I think these values will go if he takes over and takes it private."\par \par \uc2 The charge came as the Takeover Panel gave Mr Green a month to make a formal bid or walk away for six months. The ultimatum - which followed a request from M&S - comes more than five weeks after Mr Green announced his intention to bid.\par \par \uc2 The owner of Arcadia and BHS has since put forward two proposals - the most recent worth "not less than" 370p-a-share in cash. M&S rejected both a and Mr Green has yet to table a formal bid. The shares stood at 360p last night.\par \par \uc2 The Panel had issued 12 "put up or shut up" statements since the start of 2002. In all but three cases, the potential bidder walked away.\par \par \uc2 Mr Green said the deadline made no difference. "So what? What does it change?" he said. His ability to bid depended on obtaining information about the M&S pension scheme, he added. Mr Green has sought a meeting with the trustees, who will meet today to consider their response.\par \par \uc2 The deadline was welcomed by Martin Cholwill, UK equity fund manager at Axa Investment Managers, a top-10 M&S shareholder. "We've been in the middle of a phoney war for a while," he said.\par \par \uc2 David Varney, chairman of BITC, acknowledged the award would be controversial but said: "We think [corporate responsibility] is an important ingredient of a successful business. If you fall short on something else, it doesn't have the capacity to compensate. But it can speed your recovery if you have a problem." Mr Varney is also chairman of MMO,the mobile operator, where Paul Myners, M&S's interim chairman, is a director.\par \par \uc2 Ms Cleverdon said: "Anybody looking at [M&S] would discover there are a lot of values in there which had added to the financial value.\par \par \uc2 "You would destroy that at your peril." By contrast with Mr Green, Mr Rose had a record of doing "the things which help to build stronger values among employees, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and communities", she added. .\par \par \uc2 Mr Rose told the FT he was committed to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "I hope to be here, an d if I am here, it will be part of the business." Mark Goyder, director of Tomorrow's Company, the business think-tank, and one of the judges of the top award, challenged the future leaders of M&S to maintain its record of responsible behaviour or return the award. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 mks : \uc2 Marks & Spencer Group PLC\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i645 : \uc2 Clothing Stores | i64 : \uc2 Retail/Wholesale | i654 : \uc2 Specialty Stores | i656 : \uc2 Mixed Retailing | iclt : \uc2 Clothing/Textiles\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c411 : \uc2 Management Moves | c42 : \uc2 Labor/Personnel Issues | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gjob : \uc2 Labor Issues | c41 : \uc2 Management Issues | gcom : \uc2 Society/Co