r, I am glad Michael Skapinker in his column "Business schools must accept their responsibilities" (July 14) tried to take an objective view of the hand-wringing that is going on among some academics in business schools.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 It is asking for the impossible to make sure that the students who go through such schools don't end up cooking the books and siphoning off money for their personal gratification. Let me say that you cannot lead a student to a subject and make him learn.\par \par \uc2 He must want to learn. In this regard, the process of education is increasingly one of interaction between students and their instructors (I prefer to use the terms participants and facilitators) as well as between students themselves.\par \par \uc2 At Universitas 21 Global, for example, we try to pass on a sense of community through discussion and debate on any number of issues that relate to each subject undertaken by our students. This open forum allows for the expression of concerns that students have about subject material or related experiences in their workplace.\par \par \uc2 Certainly, \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and business ethics cannot be dismissed. Nor can assorted cultural differences that affect how people do international business. Our students can engage in discussion about their own experiences, gaining new insights from the responses of their colleagues who are subjected to more or less legislation in the broader economy, or regulation within their own corporate domain.\par \par \uc2 As for management consultancies and investment banks recruiting people and teaching them what they need in a fraction of the time of an MBA programme, I wish them good luck.\par \par \uc2 What is overlooked here is that a sound academic experience is not just about learning information in a given subject area. If that were the case, we may as well expect that reading a book is good enough.\par \par \uc2 An academic experience is about making people think about issues and topics. I believe this involves a mindset shift, one that should put a well-educated graduate in a better position to understand the complexities of the changing global \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  than could be gained from a thinner corporate training programme.\par \par \uc2 In the end, with any educational experience, responsibility rests with the individual, the company they work for and the country in which they live and operate.\par \par \uc2 For every corporate criminal exposed, there are many who uphold the ethics their businesses represent. Unfortunately, it's the bad apples that always make the news.\par \par \uc2 Cornelis A. Reiman, Vice President, Operations (Academic and Technical), Universitas 21 Global, Singapore 068808 \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gedu : \uc2 Education | nlte : \uc2 Letter to the Editor | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | niwe : \uc2 IWE Filter | nlet : \uc2 Letter | nrgn : \uc2 Routine General News | nfact : 