stright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 From Mr Jeffrey Swartz.\par \par \uc2 Sir, How refreshing to see the topic of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  get its due notice in your article "How model behaviour brings market power" (August 23). As the chief executive of a global organisation, I have experienced first-hand the growing trend in consumer expectation that asks companies to accept greater social responsibility. Like the authors, I believe that in light of this increasing consumer demand, executives do not have much choice if they wish to remain successful in the global marketplace and I contend that they should not have to choose. Doing well as a profit-minded business and doing good as a responsible corporate citizen need not be antagonistic notions and should, in fact, be inextricably linked.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 It is my hope that your article and others like it may cause some of the more "short-sighted" thinkers - those who insist that the business of business is nothing more than earning a return for shareholders - to reconsider their position. Is there profit to be gained by being socially responsible? Absolutely. Research shows that eight out of 10 consumers, all things being equal, will make a moral choice about the goods and services they buy. Increasingly, brands that are synonymous with ethical behaviour and responsible business are the ones that will succeed, and those that continue to ignore their role and responsibility as citizens of the global marketplace will lose.\par \par \uc2 I agree that the idea of standardising products, packaging and communication may not be desirable or effective across cultures but, given the current climate change towards more socially aware consumers, I suggest that the "lowest common denominator" may in fact be \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It is a concept that crosses all boundaries - geographical, cultural and economic. Throughout the world, people may not share the same tastes or prefer the same products, but the desire to improve the strength of our neighbourhoods, the well-being of our \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the quality of life in our communities is truly universal and indisputable. Consumers have every right to hold global brands to higher ethical standards, and I hope it's a trend that continues to grow. They are not asking for anything we should not already be demanding of ourselves.\par \par \uc2 Jeffrey Swartz, President and CEO, The Timberland Company, Stratham, NH 03885, US \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20040827U210.023\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\wi