idctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PG\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 Page 2\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2004 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 This is the seventh year we have conducted this global survey of Chief Executive Officer (CEO) opinion, and this year we have again achieved interviews with more than 1,000 respondents - and this is across 25 countries.\par \par \uc2 The core of the survey remains consistent over time, identifying those companies and business leaders globally that are most respected by their peers and the reasons for those choices. In addition, to reflect the increasingly competitive \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  in which companies are operating, we have identified those that are seen to excel in areas such as corporate governance, social responsibility and - new for this year - innovation.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 First, chief executives were asked to nominate three companies in the world they most respect. They were then asked to select three companies they most respect in their industry sector in the world.\par \par \uc2 Each chief executive was also asked to identify three business leaders they most respect in the world. These questions were asked in all the previous surveys. In all cases, and for all subsequent questions, respondents were asked to give reasons for their nominations.\par \par \uc2 In the last four years of the survey, CEOs were also asked to nominate three companies that best delivered on creating the most value for their shareholders. To provide a contrast to CEO opinion, this question was also put to more than 150 fund managers worldwide.\par \par \uc2 For the last three years, CEOs were asked to name three companies in their country or region that they most respect and for a consecutive year they were also asked to nominate three companies in the world that have the most effective corporate governance, and the companies in the world that best demonstrate their commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 To again provide a contrast to CEO opinion, more than 150 media commentators and non-governmental organisations (NGO) worldwide were asked the questions on corporate governance and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Two new questions were added to this year's survey. The first asked CEOs to identify three companies globally that demonstrate the best product or service innovation, and this was also asked of the fund managers. The other addition to the survey was an opportunity for CEOs to nominate an individual in history or today they would ask to join their company board or leadership team.\par \par \uc2 The fieldwork was undertaken between August and October 2004, principally by telephone interview but in some cases by written questionnaire or face-to-face interviews. As in previous years, the survey participants come not just from publicly-quoted organisations, but also from large subsidiaries and private companies across the 25 countries.\par \par \uc2 The results are weighted by the GDP figure of the respondent's country (the only measure available across all respondents). This is both to ensure consistency with previous years' results, and to reflect that, rightly or wrongly, there are different levels of global impact achieved by views expressed in different economies. This approach applies to the CEO, fund manager and media/NGO surveys.\par \par \uc2 To ensure that we "smooth out" any single country bias, we have once again applied a minimum qualification level of five nominations to each table, apart from the World's Most Respected Companies by Industry Sector and within individual Country, where a minimum of three nominations was required.\par \par \uc2 Importantly, we have analysed the unprompted reasons given behind nominations, providing a valuable insight into what factors drive respect for companies and business leaders.\par \par \uc2 The survey methodology provides the ability to track changes in position for companies over time as well as the reasons behind the nomination. This allows an in-depth and credible look at the opinions of CEOs and other relevant stakeholders globally on the most respected companies and business leaders in the world.There are 52 tables in all. They include 17 sector tables and 25 country tables - all appear online at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ft.com/wmrc2004Judith"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.ft.com/wmrc2004Judith}}}\uc2  Nicholl is head of research information at PricewaterhouseCoopers: Judith.nicholl@uk.pwc.com \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20041119S502.071\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c41 : \uc2 Manageme