mkins is right to say that companies such as Wal-Mart and Tesco have a "public relations problem" caused by being too big, the solution is not just based on PR puffery and the vanity of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as he seems to suggest ("The curse of success is that giants are seen as monsters" January 25). In fact, it is about how they behave and how they use their power.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Mr Tomkins suggests that reputation management consultants could help Tesco, but I am not sure they could in the way he envisages. One of the biggest mistakes made by companies in the UK (encouraged by PR companies) is to think that managing their reputation is about "PR" and "the messages". In fact, reputation management is about how you treat every stakeholder in the business and meet the expectations of those people in whose lives you play a part.\par \par \uc2 Tesco therefore needs to be paying its suppliers on time and enforcing fair payment terms on those suppliers. It needs to be paying its employees fairly and keeping promises on rewards and development. It should be transparent with investors and aware of the need to balance the requirements of short-term, medium-term and long-term investors.\par \par \uc2 The company must also engage openly with the government and regulators, make sure it has an open dialogue with activists of any sort, and deal openly with the media. It should also keep delivering to customers what they expect of it.\par \par \uc2 PR comes in by promoting how Tesco uses its power fairly and openly without harming the economic, social and physical \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If Tesco is not doing that, there is nothing PR can do. Much of reputation management is common sense, but it is always a surprise to find how many companies do not have it.\par \par \uc2 Paul Goldsmith, Associate Director, Reputation Institute UK, Cass Business School, London EC1Y 8TZ \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20050201L218.026\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 tsco : \uc2 Tesco PLC\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i641 : \uc2 Food Retailing | i83952