0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Businesses that take environmental and social issues seriously will be best placed to gain access to capital in the future, a World Bank executive has told FTfm.\par \par \uc2 Rachel Kyte, \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social director of the International Finance Corporation, the private finance arm of the World Bank, says that the understanding of risk is changing among financial companies as environmental and social issues rise up the agenda.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 In the commercial banking sector, 28 institutions have signed up to the Equator Principles, a set of guidelines for addressing environmental and social issues in project finance that were developed at a meeting called by the IFC in 2002. As a result, 80 per cent of project finance loans now have environmental conditions attached to them. "Companies that can manage their environmental risks better . . . can position themselves as leaders in the market and in terms of gaining access to capital," says Ms Kyte, speaking in her office in Washington.\par \par \uc2 Companies, particularly in the developed world, started taking \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  more seriously because of the growing risks to their reputations, the fear of litigation and the global reach of liability. But, says Ms Kyte, there has to be a further incentive for companies to improve their corporate behaviour. "If you are a good performer, you want to know how you will be rewarded for that. If you are managing your risks better, then you should get access to financing that guys who aren't managing their risks can't."\par \par \uc2 The IFC invests in emerging markets and develops local currency instruments to build financial markets and provide access to capital for entrepreneurs. "In the next three to four years, the financial markets will be driving a lot of the improvements in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and environmental management," says Ms Kyte.\par \par \uc2 Last year, the UN Global Compact, a voluntary corporate citizenship network focusing on human rights, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labour and fighting corruption, launched Who Cares Wins, a project focusing on connecting financial markets to environmental, social and governance criteria. Twenty investment companies, controlling Dollars 6,000bn (Pounds 3,000bn) in assets, signed up to the initiative. "For the first time, we had major players in the financial world, like Goldman Sachs, talking about how to take a longer term view," Ms Kyte says.\par \par \uc2 The Equator Principles started the ball rolling. Banks signed up to the principles because they had suffered concerted campaigns by NGOs after investing in projects such as the Three Gorges dam in China.\par \par \uc2 "But in very short order, those banks started seeing a competitive advantage. They could attract good risk businesses by managing these issues better and now some of the leading Equator banks are using environmental and social corporate governance factors to assess their clients and asking whether they want to be the banker for this company and how it needs to improve," she says. Already, she says, analysts and fund managers are "seeking opportunities to make their clients more robust for the long term" through governance, environmental and social factors.\par \par \uc2 As more companies in emerging markets become global players, or invest in developing markets, they are having to take CSR issues into account.\par \par \uc2 "Take Olan, an Indonesian agribusiness company involved in cashews, cocoa and coffee. Demand in Europe and the US, and the start of sophisticated demand in emerging markets such as India and Brazil, means they have to say at every step of their supply chain, from the individual farmer upwards, what they did," Ms Kyte says. "This is an Indonesian company being a global player by being socially responsible. They believe they can go head-to-head with (companies) like Nestle by doing this."\par \par \uc2 The change in the investment climate is spreading, Ms Kyte believes. "Three of the four biggest Brazilian banks have strict environmental and social standards, and (the IFC) has a Dollars 50m line of credit with Banco Real that you can only access if you are an environmentally positive business. We thought this would be just a niche experiment, but it would be easy to double that line of credit tomorrow."\par \par \uc2 The next step in the process, Ms Kyte says, is to extend the CSR message throughout emerging markets, in particular to SMEs. Only 0.1 per cent of socially responsible investment goes to emerging markets.\par \par \uc2 The IFC's environmental and social supremo has a message for fund managers, too. "SRI has played a very important role, but as we are moving into the mainstream, we feel positive incentives have a little bit more traction than negative signals."\par \par \uc2 There has been a complete shift, she believes, in the way we think about sustainable development. "The last time the UK chaired the G8, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  was seen as something that only governments would discuss. Now the private sector has a key role in the delivery of environmental and development objectives, with financial markets front and centre of that effort. This has been a momentous change." \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20050321S507.133\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ifc : \uc2 International Finance Corp\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i814 : \uc2 Banking | i8150106 : \uc2 Development Banking | ibnk : \uc2 Banking/Credit\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\li