uc2 More US companies are following the European trend for publishing lengthy environmental and social disclosures in addition to their increasingly voluminous financial reports.\par \par \uc2 United Technologies, a conglomerate that includes Black Hawk helicopters among its products, was the latest to launch a separate "responsibility" report last week detailing everything from water consumption to accident rates.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Ford announced a major expansion to its existing corporate citizenship report by promising a new climate change study with estimates of all greenhouse gas emissions, including those of its 6.8m vehicles sold annually.\par \par \uc2 Hewlett-Packard and Gap won top prize in the increasingly competitive industry awards for corporate responsibility reports with two entries totalling 118 pages.\par \par \uc2 Campaigners say the growing quantity and quality of these publications reflect the wider mood of accountability demanded following reforms such as Sarbanes-Oxley.\par \par \uc2 As asbestos and other environmental liabilities loom large in the minds of investors, more companies are choosing to err on the side of greater disclosure, not least as a way of improving their public image.\par \par \uc2 "But it is not just because they are under pressure," said Timothy Smith, director of socially responsive investing at Walden Asset Management. "A number of companies see themselves as telling their story and believe it is good business too."\par \par \uc2 George David, chief 