 \uc2 Mr. Murray grudgingly concedes that GE's "self-regulation" serves both its self-interest and the public good. Mr. Murray calls this "a good trick." No, it's not. It's good business. Other companies and industries, engaged in a similar calculus, have spurred the successful development of technologies such as hybrid automobiles. These are rational activities undertaken with an eye on shareholder welfare as well as stakeholder welfare. The two need not be at odds. \b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  isn't premised on the belief that businesses have some inchoate, undefined and unbounded duty to "do good." Rather, the simple and unremarkable point is that businesses should take responsibility for their impact on society and on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It is in the long-term interest of their owners that they do so. Adam Smith wouldn't likely have concluded otherwise.\par \par \uc2 Phillip H. Rudolph\par \par \uc2 Partner\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  Practice Group\par \par \uc2 Foley Hoag LLP\par \par \uc2 Washington \par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=wjco20050606000017"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | nlte : \uc2 Letter to the Editor | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | niwe : \uc2 IWE Filter | nlet 