 \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A group of Colombian farmers are preparing to launch a GBP15m legal claim against BP, alleging that their land was ruined and their livelihoods wrecked by the creation of an oil pipeline.\par \par \uc2 Lawyers for about 65 farmers say they will launch group litigation the closest thing to a class action in the UK at the High Court in London in the next few weeks.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The legal team spent this week in Medellin signing up dozens of farmers to "no win, no fee deals" in order to bring the claim against BP Exploration.\par \par \uc2 The action centres on a pipeline owned by Ocensa, a company in which BP holds a minority stake. The farmers claim construction of the pipeline destroyed watercourses and caused soil erosion on their land, making fish, cattle and crop farming as well as gold mining impossible.\par \par \uc2 In addition, the farmers, who are claiming as much as GBP250,000 each, insist that their families were terrorised by soldiers and paramilitaries who were charged with keeping the pipeline secure. Leigh, Day &Co, the farmers' British lawyers, are not alleging that BP had any involvement in incidents involving armed forces.\par \par \uc2 However, a letter from the lawyers to BP outlining the claim says: "What we are saying is that in entering into contracts with many of the farmers, BP took advantage of the regime of terror brought about by the army and paramilitaries, the lack of education of the farmers, the lack of available legal representation in the area, and even took steps to sideline the obtaining of legal advice when it was available."\par \par \uc2 Some cases have been brought in the Colombian courts, but the English solicitors said the case should be heard in the UK because the claimants had been unable to seek justice locally because of the difficulty in finding lawyers to represent them. Martyn Day, of Leigh, Day &Co, said one lawyer had been killed by paramilitaries and another was forced to flee the country.\par \par \uc2 The issue surfaced at BP's annual meeting in April, where Peter Sutherland, its chairman, said the company had fully investigated the claims and the landowners had been compensated "at market price levels, I think they received an average of about $11,000 each".\par \par \uc2 The oil group said: "BP believes that the pipeline companies (and the BP companies holding minority interests in the pipelines), have fulfilled their obligations, both from a legal and a \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  standpoint.\par \par \uc2 "The landowners neighbouring the rights of way of the Ocensa and ODC pipelines were fairly compensated during construction, and the land has been theirs to use ever since. Third party validation such as the Colombian Ministry of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 's report supports BP's position.\par \par \uc2 "BP's lawyers are in correspondence with Leigh Day &Co, and the pipelines continue to implement their social investment strategies throughout."\par \par \uc2 But Mr Day said the compensation paid had been too little while only about half of the claimants had received any money. He added: "We are confident that the High Court will decide this is the only place that justice can be done." \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 43021150\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i13 : \uc2 Crude Oil/Natural Gas | i1 : \uc2 Energy\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gcrim : \uc2 Crime/Courts | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gcns : \uc2 National Security\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl