c2 Who knows what goes through the minds of property tycoons as they commission buildings with ever improved environmental features? Is it all about branding a building, or a genuine commitment to green issues?\par \par \uc2 Either way, there is no doubt that, in the developed world, architects and developers are paying more attention to sustainability.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Perhaps the issue reached its apex when the designers of the replacement for the World Trade Center in New York wanted to put a wind farm on the upper floors. It would have generated electricity for 10 per cent of the skyscraper's needs.\par \par \uc2 As it happens, the architects behind the 1,776 foot high structure have redrawn the tower, erasing the wind turbines from the plan. Nevertheless a host of new skyscrapers in the US have environmental features.\par \par \uc2 Elsewhere, architects are introducing waterless urinals, improved insulation and a host of other features.\par \par \uc2 The trend has also touched industrial property, where some companies are building solar panels on warehouses, or using the roofs to collect rainwater, or erecting wind turbines on site. Gazeley, owned by Wal-Mart, has plans for warehouses with grass roofs.\par \par \uc2 Housebuilders, too, in Europe and the US, are incorporating more features such as improved insulation and alternative power generation in their schemes.\par \par \uc2 "Those who dismiss this as a passing fad or public relations 'greenwash' do so at their peril," says Nick Axford at CB Richard Ellis.\par \par \uc2 Sometimes environmental features are used as a means to overcome planning hurdles. From a commercial point of view, too, a green brand is attractive to consumers - although it is not clear how much of a premium they are prepared to pay.\par \par \uc2 "Without any kind of subsidies there are questions about the financial viability of such projects," says Angus McIntosh, research head at King Sturge and an exponent of sustainability.\par \par \uc2 Sir Stuart Lipton, of Stanhope, one of Britain's leading developers, says there should be a Treasury-driven incentive for occupiers to take green buildings. "Agents say that tenants will not pay the additional service charge," he says.\par \par \uc2 In the wider sense, sustainability is also about creating communities where people can live, work and play and which are pedestrianised rather than car dominated.\par \par \uc2 Against the backdrop of the Kyoto Agreement, most developed countries have agreed to cut greenhouse gas emissions. Many have launched drives to cut emissions. Other initiatives have included drives to use more wood in construction.\par \par \uc2 Some developers are introducing combined heat and power (CHP) in new buildings as well as other indirect ways to improve sustainability. Stanhope, for example, uses a single warehouse on the edge of a city to improve logistics and cut down on lorry trips. "It means you don't need 30 different trucks carrying product to the site, that is real energy efficiency," says Sir Stuart.\par \par \uc2 The wider debate includes the issue of whether new build can ever be an improvement on an old one, given that the cost of replacement will often outweigh subsequent energy savings.\par \par \uc2 For now, while some property companies have put a major emphasis on \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , others may not feel such strong pressures. A handful of institutional investors, such as Co-op Insurance Services, take into account sustainability issues. But this is a minority view. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20050928S109.355\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i16 : \uc2 Electricity/Gas Utilities | i16101 : \uc2 Electric Power Generation | ireest : \uc2 Real Estate | i1 : \uc2 Energy | icre : \uc2 Construction/Real Estate\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gclimt : \uc2 Climate Change | genv : \uc2 Environmental News | gqual : \uc2 Air/Water/Land Quality | nanl : \uc2 Analysis | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gglobe : \uc2 Global/World Issues | gwea : \uc2 Weather | ncat : \uc2 Content Types\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri