th.\par \par \uc2 Sir, Tobias Buck and Stephanie Kirchgaessner ("Brussels braces for a US lobbying invasion", October 3) give the impression that European lobbyists are inactive, with purely a mandate to monitor new legislation. By contrast, the article suggests, our US lobbyist colleagues will work with their clients in order to achieve legislative results. Anyone who has witnessed Reach will know that European lobbyists are not quite so timid, and in that respect we probably share a lot of common values, even if our more modest approach distinguishes us.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Europe has realised that lobbying casts many images; most often it is associated with ugly politics. For example, in Europe political donations are frowned on whereas in the US it is commonplace. Of growing interest in Europe is that corporate lobbying should be fully integrated with \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . In a report "Influencing power: reviewing the conduct and content of corporate lobbying" earlier this year by SustainAbility and WWF, the authors argued that lobbyists should take leadership for promoting better legislation. In this respect, European industry is learning that stricter and stronger protection of the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social policy should be central to\par \par \uc2 our policy ambitions. For these reasons, I am not sure the same brash US lobbying techniques described by the authors are welcome in Europe.\par \par \uc2 Nick Farnsworth,\par \par \uc2 ADS Insight,\par \par \uc2 B-1000 Brussels \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20051006E114.008\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gdip : \uc2 International Relations | nlet : \uc2 Letter | nlte : \uc2 Letter to the Editor | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gpir : \uc2 Politics/International Relations | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfce : \uc2 FC&E Exclusion Filter | niwe : \uc2 IWE Filter | nrgn : \uc2 Routine General News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 belg : \uc2 Belgium | usa : \uc2 United States | benluxz : \uc2 Benelux Countries | eecz : \uc2 European Unio