0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A commitment to sustainable business and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  can be a significant help to companies seeking to attract and retain talented staff.\par \par \uc2 Employees are more likely than not to be sympathetic to the aims of making a business sustainable but research has shown that many may be unsure of what \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  means for them in their jobs.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 In some companies, such policies are not taken seriously because there is lack of direction from senior management and no board level vision of what a sustainable business looks like.\par \par \uc2 According to Forum for the Future, the leading sustainable development charity in the UK, the way for companies to involve their employees more fruitfully in their quest to become more sustainable involves two important undertakings.\par \par \uc2 First, the company must have a senior executive to link sustainable business activities into core strategy and make sure it is translated into individual activity.\par \par \uc2 Second, after staff have been trained on the issues, their behaviour needs to be incentive driven through linking their "sustainable performance" to pay rises or career progression.\par \par \uc2 Sally Uren, director of the Forum business programme, says: "A proactive approach to sustainability issues can harness and maximise potential of employees and deliver greater individual satisfaction as well as long-term value creation for business."\par \par \uc2 One example of a "sustainable" friendly business model is that of WebEx, a provider of online web conferencing and collaborative business applications.\par \par \uc2 The WebEx technology allows users to see each other and talk, much like a video-conference, but also lets them share documents on screen, such as presentations and drawings.\par \par \uc2 The idea is that such meetings remove the need for face to face contact and all paperwork is on line.\par \par \uc2 In an \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  in which companies are trying to reduce the amount of money they spend on business travel, the option is proving popular.\par \par \uc2 "When you consider that the average round trip from London to New York emits 1.2 tonnes of CO2 per person into the atmosphere, the environmental impact of global business travel becomes clear," says Silvia Jensen, European marketing director at WebEx.\par \par \uc2 "If translated into watts of electricity, the same amount of carbon dioxide would allow a business person to meet online for nearly 25 weeks continuously."\par \par \uc2 WebEx, which employs 1,800 globally, says its own staff travel is very limited.\par \par \uc2 Clients include Aviva, the insurance group, which last year saved $100,000 after using the technology, and Toshiba.\par \par \uc2 WebEx has a market capitalisation of about $1bn and turnover of $300m.\par \par \uc2 Rabobank, the largest Dutch bank, has been rated the most sustainable large bank in Europe and second in the world after Westpac, the Australian bank.\par \par \uc2 The ratings are given by Zurich based SAM group, an independent asset management company specialising in sustainability investments.\par \par \uc2 Launched in 1999 with Dow Jones Indexes, the group of sustainability indices tracks the performance of companies that are industry leaders in terms of sustainability.\par \par \uc2 The ratings account for issues such as climate change, corporate governance, supply chain standards and labour conditions.\par \par \uc2 Rabobank is a good example of an organisation that trains and provides incentives to its staff in how to be more sustainably effective.\par \par \uc2 The bank started a green car leasing policy with its employees.\par \par \uc2 Rabobank staff used to be allowed to change company cars depending on salary.\par \par \uc2 The Dutch government rates cars according to their energy use.\par \par \uc2 A car with an A, B or C rating is one that better conserves energy.\par \par \uc2 All leasing cars at Rabobank now have to be in the A, B or C category.\par \par \uc2 "Our top managers can no longer drive the fancy cars they want.\par \par \uc2 "People were cynical in the beginning but now they accept it and think it's a good thing," says Jean-Pierre Sweerts, head of sustainable development for Rabobank.\par \par \uc2 All energy consumed by the bank is wind-driven so the company is CO2 neutral and all paper is sourced from sustainable forests.\par \par \uc2 "We hope that our employees take these practices home," says Mr Sweerts.\par \par \uc2 "They can be proud of the bank and its sustainable practices. We have to be commercially driven but we look further than the profit line.\par \par \uc2 "Society likes it more, our employees like it more and our clients like it more."\par \par \uc2 Even the coffee the company buys is ecological and comes from small farmers who get paid a higher than normal price for their beans.\par \par \uc2 This initiative was started by an employee. Managers at Rabobank are measured against their ability to meet sustainability targets.\par \par \uc2 Every business unit has its own sustainable development goals and employees are encouraged to do extra work in the community. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 44902398\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gjob : \uc2 Labor Issues | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gcom : \uc2 Society/Community/Work\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\wid